{"title":"Trek Teases Steel Full Suspension Bike, But Production May Be a PipeDream","link":"https://bikerumor.com/trek-teases-steel-full-suspension-bike-pipedream/","date":1730933233000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-hero-jpeg.webp\" width=\"722\" height=\"705\" alt=\"(Photo / Trek Bikes)\" /></p>\n<p>Today on Instagram, with the caption “Should we make this?”, Trek Bicycles teased a possible new full-suspension mountain bike. They’re calling it the PipeDream. The IG post continues by saying that the bike was designed by Trek’s Industrial Designer, Kyle Neuser, and “crafted by Trek’s prototype lab.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-Kyle-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"717\" height=\"580\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-Kyle-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Trek Prototype PipeDream Steel Full Sus Kyle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-Kyle-jpeg.webp 717w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-Kyle-297x240.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-Kyle-120x97.webp 120w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo / Trek Bikes)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>According to the post, the geo is borrowed from <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-top-fuel-gen-4/\" target=\"_blank\">the new Top Fuel</a>, as well as the rear end and rocker link. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-rear-end-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"722\" height=\"870\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-rear-end-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Trek Prototype PipeDream Steel Full Sus rear end\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-rear-end-jpeg.webp 722w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-rear-end-249x300.webp 249w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-rear-end-100x120.webp 100w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Instagram post mentions that it was Kyle’s vision to “combine the natural damping of steel with the proven geo and pedaling performance of the new Top Fuel”. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Steel is Still Real</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-bolt-on-shock-mount-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"703\" height=\"874\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-bolt-on-shock-mount-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Trek Prototype PipeDream Steel Full Sus bolt-on shock mount\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-bolt-on-shock-mount-jpeg.webp 703w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-bolt-on-shock-mount-241x300.webp 241w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-bolt-on-shock-mount-97x120.webp 97w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The PipeDram is running bolt-on aluminum shock mounts that allow for future suspension tuning. It’s also nice to see some exposed cable routing on the classic skinny steel tubes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-head-tube-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"722\" height=\"787\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-head-tube-jpeg.webp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-head-tube-jpeg.webp 722w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-head-tube-275x300.webp 275w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-head-tube-110x120.webp 110w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-numbers-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"658\" height=\"874\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-numbers-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Trek Prototype PipeDream Steel Full Sus numbers\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-numbers-jpeg.webp 658w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-numbers-226x300.webp 226w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-numbers-90x120.webp 90w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The paint scheme on the PipeDream is meant to reflect the colorways of the steel Trek bikes of the 80s and 90s – their attempt to remind everyone that steel can still meet the demands that today’s trails dish out.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-external-routing-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"722\" height=\"869\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-external-routing-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Trek Prototype PipeDream Steel Full Sus external routing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-external-routing-jpeg.webp 722w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-external-routing-249x300.webp 249w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Trek-Prototype-PipeDream-Steel-Full-Sus-external-routing-100x120.webp 100w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This “prototype” checks a lot of boxes. It is both modern and retro, and very good-looking. This is not the first nor the last bike company to make a kick-ass steel full-suspension MTB, but it’s rare to see something along these lines from one of the manufacturing giants.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Yay, or Nay?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For more on this bike, or to give a Trek a thumbs-up or thumbs-down on the PipeDream. Let them know if they should move forward with production, check out their <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/DCCXEv5PxsL/?img_index=1\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram</a> account.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/\" target=\"_blank\">TrekBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-teases-steel-full-suspension-bike-pipedream/\">Trek Teases Steel Full Suspension Bike, But Production May Be a PipeDream</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f62476cd07234c7fd5cd8ac1d1a6834dae1ff8065484e6b348ec5d607923f157","category":"Cycling"}